For the second time, youths in Niger state grounded activities in Minna, the Niger state capital in their continued protest against insecurity, lack of electricity and bad roads. The protest started from Mobile roundabout to the Minna city gate where they blocked the entrance from Abuja to Minna. The demands of the protesters was foe the state government to end banditry in all the local government areas in the state, repair the bad roads and ensure the people in the state are given adequate power supply. The protesters say that they will not leave until the state Governor comes out to listen to their plights.